==English==

===Proverb===
'''[[the]] [[ends]] [[justify]] [[the]] [[means]]'''
# Morally wrong actions are sometimes necessary to achieve morally right outcomes.
# Actions can only be considered morally right or wrong by virtue of the morality of the outcome.

